    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-24T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-24T02:00:00-05:00" n="493"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d493">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11–2445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Robertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-24T14:00:00+07:00"
                            >November 24, 1945—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 24—1:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2029. In telegram dated November 20 Secretary Stevens<note n="66"
                        xml:id="d493fn66">Harry S. Stevens, Second Secretary of Embassy in China, on
                        detail at Peiping.</note> at Peiping reports in substance as follows:</p>
                <p>Military information covering last 3 weeks reflects progressive deterioration of
                    Central Government’s military position vis-à-vis Chinese Communists in North
                    China. Communists are concentrated along the eastern part of Great Wall,
                    especially at passes, resulting in serious disorders in Chahar and Suiyuan, and
                    along Peiping-Liaoning and Peiping-Suiyuan railways. Communists have repeatedly
                    destroyed sections of Peiping-Liaoning Railway between Chinwangtao and Kailan
                    coal fields. Coal trains guarded by U.S. Marines and Marine plane[s?] have been
                    fired on in this region. Communists’ siege of Kueisui intensified during first 2
                    weeks of November and Communist advance on Paotou under way. Communist activity
                    is also reported on <pb facs="0678" n="668" xml:id="pg_668"/> Honan-Hopeh
                    border. The Peiping area is calm, with Communists controlling hills believed to
                    be only Communist militia. Commodity prices continue to advance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
